metadata.name: Artifact #78
metadata.description:
This project is about uncovering artifacts.

Each piece is determined by approximately 15 parameters. This allows for a multitude of possible forms, and each iteration is an artifact to be discovered within the multidimensional space.

This work is focused around discovery. It is about exploring the space of the algorithm, shedding light on its many forms, and sometimes finding artifacts of the real world embedded within them.

Technically, this work is a composition of three primary elements: Voronoi tessellations, orthographic projection, and the depth-sort algorithm.
The latter of these is integral to the rendering mechanism. It works intuitively, drawing distant objects before near objects, evaluating the distance of each object according to its geometric center. It does this precisely, and in doing so, it can produce interesting visual artifacts, drawing some shapes in an unexpected order.



This has been a fascinating study, bringing light to unreal shapes and forms, and uncovering artifacts in an impossible space.

I hope you enjoy it,
Nat Sarkissian





Technical Notes:
- Append “&mag=N” to the end of the URL in live mode to specify a resolution multiplier. It will render the image N times larger than the size of your window. If you have specified anything greater than 1, a download will start automatically once the rendering is done.

metadata.name: Southern Gothic #46
metadata.description:
“Southern Gothic” is my debut release on the fxhash platform. The project is created entirely through code. All copyrights are released to the holder of each image output, even for commercial purposes.

“Southern Gothic” borrows its name from the literary genre made famous by writers like Flannery O’Connor and Carson McCullers. Rather than illustrating a singular setting, the code generates an entire rural townscape, thereby, blurring the boundaries between representation and narrative. The individual scenes are framed frontally with an intentionally flat aesthetic character, referencing traditional folk art of the American South. The absence of human figures within these scenes adds to their overwhelming sense of darkness and forlorn. Observing multiple scenes side-by-side, one may even get the strange feeling that something terrible has happened (or is about to happen) in this rural landscape.

Pressing the down arrow saves the coded output as a .png image.

metadata.name: FairyCells II #292
metadata.description:
FairyCells II is intended as a logical continuation of the first FairyCells series. By dropping the plotter drawing constraint, new perspectives for exploration appeared.
This is how these cells began to intertwine, live together, mutate and change color, like an evolving system.

What surprises me the most in this new series, is the stories appearing behind each new composition. See how these abstracts shapes can come to life and narrate us things through our imagination.

Each color palette takes us into a different world, drawing a very specific atmosphere.

As me, let yourself be carried away by these stories 💫 !

Artwork by Julien_Espagnon, 2022.

Control : Press « S » to save the image as a PNG.

At the beginning, a program is generated from various commands. Further, the agent, following this program, forms a certain structure, which can be seen in the picture.

metadata.name: Morpheus #105
metadata.description:
A spinning, shapeshifting Morpheus which constantly changes form. 

3 Different Rotation types: 
Normal - 55% chance
Enhanced - 25% chance
Max - 20% chance

18 Palettes: 
15 with a 6% chance to appear
2 rare (Reds 4%, Greens 4%) 
1 very rare (Mono 2%)

Mouse click - or tap screen change all of the background colors

Some key functions: 
s - save output as png 
r - change from the standard rotation to a random different rotation amount
1 - randomly change the background color for the top left
2 - randomly change the background color for the top right	
3 - randomly change the background color for the bottom left
4 - randomly change the background color for the bottom right
c - Change the border and stroke colors of the Morpheus

Made in p5.js
P1xelboy 
May 2022

metadata.name: this is a bird #54
metadata.description:
"Imagine an infant lying in its cradle and the window is open and into the room comes something marvelous, mysterious, glittering, shedding light of many colors, movement, sound, a transformative hierophany of integrated perception... and the child is enthralled.

And then the mother comes into the room and she says to the child 'That's a bird, baby. That's a bird.' Instantly, the complex wave of the angel peacock iridescent transformative mystery is collapsed into the word. All mystery is gone.

The child learns 'this is a bird, this is a bird'. And by the time we’re five or six years old all the mystery of reality has been carefully tiled over with words."
-- Terence McKenna

metadata.name: Origin-a-tions II: Formation #5
metadata.description:
Nothing stays the same as they first origin-a-ted. Things are constantly changing from one form to another. Only those who can see all these formation steps in order can really grasp the true nature of things.

Origin-a-tions is a three-parts series of generative artwork, started with Part I: Creation and continuing now with Part II: Formation, that depicts one possible variation of how things may be originating.

metadata.name: inter(rupt)ions #25
metadata.description:
"Taking into account the fact that everything and everyone is made of atoms, then all living things and objects are breakable. But what about the things that are not tangible? How do they break? 'inter(rupt)ions' is an interpretation and visualization of a good feeling, being broken, separated and shaped into lines and geometric forms, whether that feeling is trust, hope, respect or love."

AI on canvas (2022)
